'''Apple TV''' is a [[digital media player]] and [[microconsole]] developed and sold by [[Apple Inc.]] It is a small [[networking hardware|network appliance]] and entertainment device that can receive digital data for visual and audio content such as music, video, video games, or the screen display of certain other devices, and play it on a connected [[television set]] or other video display.

Apple TV is an [[HDMI]]-compliant source device.<ref name=":1" /> To use it for viewing, it has to be connected to an [[enhanced-definition television|enhanced-definition]] or [[high-definition television|high-definition]] [[widescreen]] television via an HDMI cable. The device has no integrated controls and can only be controlled remotely, either by an [[Apple Remote]] or [[Siri Remote]] control device (which is included with Apple TV) using its infrared/Bluetooth capability, by the [[Remote (Apple software)|Apple TV Remote app]] (downloadable from [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]]) on numerous Apple devices using its [[Wi-Fi]] capability, or by some third-party gaming controllers and [[remote control|infrared remotes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Apple TV: Can I program my universal remote to work with Apple TV |url=https://www.apple.com/shop/question/answers/readonly/tag/appletv/can-i-program-my-universal-remote-to-work-with-apple-tv/QFPXHYX7XY9HCCFYC |publisher=[[Apple Inc.]] |accessdate=24 August 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Can the Apple TV bring everything under (remote) control? |url=https://www.macworld.com/article/3011167/home-players/how-to-use-any-remote-control-with-your-apple-tv.html |website=[[Macworld]] |accessdate=24 August 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>

Apple TV runs [[software application]]s preinstalled with the system software or, for models running [[tvOS]], downloaded from Apple's [[App Store (tvOS)|tvOS App Store]] over the device's Wi-Fi connection, with the most popular being those that stream video.<ref name="AppleRefocus5" /> Major online content sources for Apple TV apps include subscription services for [[streaming television]] and film, cable and broadcast networks via [[TV Everywhere]], and major [[sports league]]s.{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}}

Its Wi-Fi capability is also used to receive content purchased or rented directly from Apple's [[ITunes Store]], transmitted from other nearby [[iDevice|iDevices]] via [[AirPlay]], or shared from [[macOS]] or [[Windows]] computers running [[ITunes]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}}

According to observers, Apple's [[list of Apple Inc. media events#Apple Special Event (March 25, 2019)|March 2019 special event]] highlighted the company's reorientation of its focus away from the Apple TV hardware, which has lagged competitors with only 13% of U.S. connected TV market share, and apps on the [[set-top box]], and toward higher revenue Apple-distributed video streaming that will be available even through competitors' devices, via the company's [[Apple TV+]] original content service and [[Apple TV Channels]] [[A la carte pay television|a la carte]] premium [[video on demand]] subscription aggregating service.<ref name="AppleRefocus1">{{cite news |url=https://www.pcmag.com/commentary/367380/apple-tv-is-the-death-of-apple-tv |title=Apple TV Is the Death of Apple TV |last=Greenwald |first=Will |website=[[PCMag.com]] |date=March 26, 2019 |access-date=March 26, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus2">{{cite news |url=https://www.fiercevideo.com/video/editor-s-corner-apple-tv-will-die-so-tv-can-live |title=Apple TV will die so TV+ can live |last=Munson |first=Ben |website=FierceVideo |date=March 26, 2019 |access-date=March 26, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus3">{{cite news |url=https://venturebeat.com/2019/03/26/apple-tvs-biggest-news-isnt-about-content-its-about-screens-you-can-watch-anywhere/ |title=Apple TVâ€™s biggest news isnâ€™t about content, itâ€™s about screens â€” you can watch anywhere |last=Lawrence |first=Dallas |website=[[VentureBeat]] |date=March 26, 2019 |access-date=March 26, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus4">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/3-ways-the-new-apple-tv-services-will-make-cord-cutting-better/ |title=3 ways the new Apple TV services will make cord cutting better |last=Hiner |first=Jason |website=[[Cnet.com]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=March 26, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus5">{{cite news |url=http://fortune.com/2019/03/24/watch-apple-event-live-stream-television-news-service/ |last=Pullen |first=John Patrick |title=Apple's Two-Word Plan for the Future of the Internet: Subscribe Now |website=[[Forbes.com]] |date=March 24, 2019 |access-date=March 25, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus6">{{cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/business/hollywood/la-fi-ct-apple-video-service-20190325-story.html |last1=Lee |first1=Wendy |last2=Faughnder |first2=Ryan |title=Apple unveils ambitious new video service intended to take on Netflix |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=March 25, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus7">{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2019/03/25/apple-event-unveils-new-premium-news-and-streaming-services/3249329002/ |title=Apple goes big on premium services: Apple TV+ streaming, News+, Arcade and new credit card |last=Baig |first=Edward C. |newspaper=[[USA Today]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=March 25, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus8">{{cite news |url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/03/25/apple-tv-channels/ |last=Hardawar |first=Devindra |title=Apple TV Channels is an a la carte way to watch your favorite networks |website=[[Engadget]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=March 25, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="AppleRefocus9">{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/apple-tv-streaming-service-1203171335/ |title=Apple Reveals New TV Streaming Service | last=Holloway |first=Daniel |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=March 26, 2019 |website=[[Variety.com]]|df=mdy-all}}</ref>
